data.title: Doctor Who Season 14: Will there be more episodes on Disney+? Complete Schedule
data.meta_description: As the renowned British sci-fi series Doctor Who launches into its 14th season, fans are eagerly awaiting a new chapter packed with exhilarating adventures and captivating narratives.
data.text:
Synopsis

As the renowned British sci-fi series Doctor Who launches into its 14th season, fans are eagerly awaiting a new chapter packed with exhilarating adventures and captivating narratives.

As the iconic British sci-fi series Doctor Who embarks on its 14th season, fans eagerly anticipate a fresh era filled with thrilling adventures and intriguing storylines. With renowned writer Russell T. Davies at the helm and a groundbreaking casting choice, the stage is set for an unforgettable journey through time and space.

The Doctor's Return: Season Premiere Details

Doctor Who Season 14 makes its much awaited debut on Disney+ starting Friday, May 10, marking the beginning of an exciting new chapter in the franchise. Viewers can look forward to weekly releases, with new episodes airing every Friday through June 21.

Streaming Schedule and Subscription Details

All episodes of Doctor Who Season 14 is available for streaming on Disney+ at 7 p.m. ET, ensuring that fans can immerse themselves in the latest adventures of the Doctor and their companions at their convenience, as per a report by Decider. Whether subscribed to the ad-supported plan at $7.99/month or the ad-free option at $13.99/month, viewers can access the new episodes with ease.

Episode Guide

Season 14 of Doctor Who consists of eight thrilling episodes, complemented by the 2023 Christmas special, "The Church on Ruby Road," which introduced the enigmatic Fifteenth Doctor. Below is a comprehensive guide to the release dates of each episode:

Episode 1, "Space Babies": Friday, May 10

Episode 2, "The Devil’s Chord": Friday, May 10

Episode 3, "Boom": Friday, May 17

Episode 4, "73 Yards": Friday, May 24

Episode 5, "Dot and Bubble": Friday, May 31

Episode 6, "Rogue": Friday, June 7

Episode 7, "The Legend of Ruby Sunday": Friday, June 14

Episode 8, "Empire of Death": Friday, June 21

Meet the Cast: A Stellar Lineup

Ncuti Gatwa leads the cast as the groundbreaking Fifteenth Doctor, accompanied by Millie Gibson in the role of companion Ruby Sunday. Joining them are a host of talented actors in recurring or guest roles, including Jemma Redgrave, Aneurin Barnard, and Anita Dobson, among others. Their diverse characters promise to enrich the Doctor's adventures with depth and intrigue.

Streaming Options for Past Seasons

While Disney+ exclusively offers Doctor Who Season 14, fans seeking to explore earlier seasons have alternative streaming options. Classic episodes from 1963 to 1989 are available on BritBox, Prime Video, and Tubi, while the modern revival (2005-present) up to Season 13 can be found exclusively on Max.

FAQs

Will there be a 14th season of Doctor Who?

Doctor Who season 14 comprises 8 episodes, with each episode being released weekly on Disney+. The premiere aired on May 10, 2024, and subsequent episodes will follow suit until June 21, 2024.

Is Jodie Whittaker in season 14 of Doctor Who?

Following the Thirteenth Doctor (Jodie Whittaker) and the Fourteenth Doctor (David Tennant), "Doctor Who" introduces its Fifteenth Doctor (Ncuti Gatwa), who debuted in the "Doctor Who Christmas Special" in late 2023.
